This paper presents a text (KAR 44), considered as a kind of **‘exorcist’s manual’**, used in Ancient Mesopotamia.

[The paper is a comparison to G. Buccellati’s [*Appendix 15.6*](http://4banks.net/Mes-rel/Excerpts/appendices_mDP.htm#15.6), describing the figure of Marduk as the prototype of the Mesopotamian exorcist.]

